          <h3>About Us</h3>
          <p><strong><i>The  India Today Group</i></strong><br>
          
          <p><strong>History-making, future-making</strong><br>
            India Today Media Institute’s birth in 2005 was a result of our Group’s recognition of a dearth of industry-ready, skilled talent in broadcast journalism. True to its original identity, we still maintain our focus on a careful marriage of skill development with responsible concept-building, so that our graduates are job-ready in both conceptual and practical terms. As we expanded our footprint and offerings in 2014, we adopted a three-pronged approach to our already individual-centric approach—to build in our students the very values that our knowledge industries both crave and appreciate:</p>
          <p> Learnability<br>
            Worldview<br>
            Employability </p>
          <p> We achieve this objective through a combination of interdisciplinary and focused methods. That combination alone can make a student imbibe all those three qualities meaningfully and fruitfully. We pride ourselves on our natural and developed advantages: Access to state-of-the-art media technology; learning from some of the best minds in the industries; unparalleled exposure to the world’s top professionals, thinkers, nation-builders and lawmakers; focus on learning coupled with application at simulated and “live” levels; and finally, our serious emphasis on employability, providing unparalleled job opportunities both within the India Today Group and in the media and communication industries nationally. </p>
          <p> ITMI could not have been founded on firmer grounding. The India Today Group's strength of understanding and delivering high-quality matter has not only rubbed off on our serious-minded institute-indeed, we carry the torch further by making a difference to the profession. </p>
          <p> The India Today Group began with a single magazine India Today in 1975. Today it is India's most diversified media group-and one of India's largest media groups, with 37 magazines, 7 radio stations, 4 TV channels, a music label, a newspaper, online and e-commerce platforms, one of Delhi's best reputed schools, and, of course, the media institute. Each of the group's businesses is committed to the most stringent standards of quality and highest standards of social responsibility. </p>
         
          <p><strong>Print and online: </strong>Our publications cover books, magazines and  newspapers in print and on the internet in a wide variety of genres, from  political and general (such as <strong><em><u><a href="/" target="_blank">India Today</a></u></em></strong>)<em>, </em>business<em> (<strong><u><a href="https://businesstoday.intoday.in/" target="_blank">Business  Today</a></u></strong>, <strong><u><a href="https://www.hbrsasia.org/" target="_blank">Harvard Business  Review</a></u></strong>),</em>lifestyle <em>(<strong><u><a href="https://cosmo.intoday.in/cosmopolitan/index.jsp" target="_blank">Cosmopolitan</a></u></strong>,<strong><u> <a href="https://menshealth.intoday.in/menshealth/index.jsp" target="_blank">Men's Health</a></u></strong>,<strong><u> Harper's  Bazaar</u></strong>), </em>and  enrichment <em>(<strong><u><a href="http://www.readersdigest.co.in/" target="_blank">Reader's Digest</a></u></strong>), </em>and enjoy wide patronage across India. <strong><em><u>Mail Today</u></em></strong><em>, </em>our group's daily newspaper, is  reputed for its quality and depth of coverage. The group's offerings are on the  online platform, <strong><em><u><a href="http://www.indiatodaygroup.com/" target="_blank">InToday</a></u></em></strong>. The prestigious <strong><em><u><a href="https://www.thomsonpress.com/" target="_blank">Thompson Press</a></u></em></strong> and India's only book club are also  part of our diversified media group.</p>
          <p><strong>Broadcast: </strong>The group's broadcast company, TV Today Network  Limited, owns&nbsp; 7 radio stations across India under the banner <strong><em><u><a href="http://oyefm.in/" target="_blank">Oye  FM</a></u></em></strong>, 4 leading television&nbsp; channels that hardly need  introduction: <strong><em><u><a href="https://aajtak.intoday.in/" target="_blank">Aaj Tak</a></u></em></strong><em>, <strong><u><a href="/" target="_blank">India Today</a></u></strong>,<strong><u> Tez</u></strong></em>and <strong><em><u><a href="https://aajtak.intoday.in/dilliaajtak/" target="_blank">Dilli  Aaj Tak</a></u></em></strong>.</p>
          <p><strong>Retail media: </strong>The group's forays into retail business started  in the 1990s with <strong><em><u><a href="https://www.musictoday.in/" target="_blank">Music Today</a></u></em></strong>, one of India's leading music labels, while  the most recent addition to this subgroup is <strong><em><u><a href="https://www.bagittoday.com/" target="_blank">Bag It Today</a></u></em></strong>,  which offers an online shopping experience.</p>
          <p> Over the  last 35 years, the group has evolved with its namesake. Through its  subscribers, readers, viewers, surfers and listeners, the India Today Group has reached out to over 50 million  consumers; reflected public opinion as well as shaped it; delivered India to the world and the world to India. With  ITMI, the Group now looks forward to changing the world of media education.</p>
